# Project Rules

Use `AGENTS.md` and `CONVENTIONS.md` as the source of truth. Keep examples aligned with the actual source tree.

## Core Rules

- Use `yarn` only.
- `yarn validate` runs `type-check`, `lint`, `format:check`, and `i18n:check`.
- Use `StyleSheet` from `react-native-unistyles`.
- Never use inline styles, color literals, or hardcoded spacing.
- Use project components from `@/common/components`.
- Translate every user-facing string and update all locale files (`en.json`, `vi.json`, `zh-CN.json`, `zh-TW.json`).
- Auth is handled only by `useAuthStore`.
- Use React Query for server state and Zustand selectors for client state.
- Use `@/services/api` for HTTP requests.
- Use `react-hook-form` with `zod/v4`.
- No `any`, no suppression comments, and no `--no-verify`.

## Repo Facts

- `app/` has `(auth)` and `(main)` route groups.
- `app/_layout.tsx` wires gesture handling, error boundary, query provider, alert provider, bottom sheet provider, camera provider, auth init, and toast.
- `src/common/components/index.ts` is the public shared-component barrel.
- `src/providers/index.ts` exports `QueryProvider`, `useAuthStore`, `useAuthInit`, `AppBottomSheetProvider`, `useAppBottomSheet`, `AppAlertProvider`, and `useAppAlert`.
